===========================================================
LeetCode 15 - 3Sum

My Mistakes & Conceptual Errors
===========================================================

1. Forgot to skip duplicate i
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Forgot to write:

if(i > 0 && nums[i] == nums[i-1])
    continue;

Learning:
If the fixed element is repeated,
the same triplets will be generated again.

===========================================================

2. Wrong while condition
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:

while(j < k && nums[j] != nums[j-1])

Learning:
Initially,

j = i + 1

So,

nums[j-1] == nums[i]

I was accidentally comparing j with i.

Correct:

while(j < k)

Duplicate handling should not be inside the loop condition.

===========================================================

3. Forgot to move pointers after finding a triplet
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:

triplets.push_back(...);

No j++ and k--.

Result:
Infinite loop because j and k never changed.

Learning:
Always move both pointers after storing
a valid triplet.

===========================================================

4. Wrong placement of j++ and k--
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Placed j++ and k-- outside the
sum == 0 block.

Learning:

j++ and k-- should happen ONLY
after a valid triplet is found.

===========================================================

5. Wrong order of operations
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Wanted to remove duplicates before
storing the triplet.

Correct Order:

Store Triplet
↓

j++
k--

↓

Skip duplicate j

↓

Skip duplicate k

Learning:
Always save the current valid answer first.

===========================================================

6. Skipping duplicates after every iteration
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Placed duplicate skipping outside
the sum == 0 block.

Learning:

Duplicate removal should happen only
after finding a valid triplet.

Otherwise valid combinations may be skipped.

===========================================================

7. Forgot duplicate handling for k
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Handled duplicates only for j.

Learning:

Duplicates can exist on both sides.

Need

while(nums[j] == nums[j-1])

AND

while(nums[k] == nums[k+1])

===========================================================

8. Wrong position of duplicate handling
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Placed duplicate loops outside
their required scope.

Learning:

Duplicate handling belongs inside
the sum == 0 block.

===========================================================

9. Brace ({ }) placement mistake
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Incorrect nesting of while loops.

Result:
Duplicate handling executed in
unexpected places.

Learning:

Always check indentation.

Every opening brace should have
a clear matching closing brace.

===========================================================

10. Thought changing j automatically handles k
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Assumed if j changes,
k will naturally become unique.

Learning:

j and k move independently.

Both pointers require separate
duplicate handling.

===========================================================

11. Didn't understand why compare with j-1 and k+1
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Confused about

nums[j] == nums[j-1]

nums[k] == nums[k+1]

Learning:

After

j++;
k--;

Current pointer should be compared
with its previous position.

===========================================================

12. Forgot loop optimization
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:

for(i = 0; i < n; i)

Learning:

Use

for(i = 0; i < n-2; i)

because at least three elements
are needed.

===========================================================

13. Initially focused on code instead of logic
-----------------------------------------------------------
Mistake:
Tried to memorize conditions.

Learning:

Understand WHY each condition exists.

Every line has a purpose.

===========================================================

Base Cases / Edge Cases
===========================================================

✔ Array size < 3
No triplet possible.

✔ All positive numbers
Answer = empty.

✔ All negative numbers
Answer = empty.

✔ Multiple duplicate elements
Need duplicate handling.

✔ Multiple valid triplets
Store every unique triplet.

✔ Already sorted array
Algorithm still works.

